      <p><h3>What is Anki?</h3>
      <p>Anki is a fantastic resource for anyone learning languages (or indeed learning anything).  It is a flashcard program that works on a <b>Spaced Repetition System (SRS)</b>.  This means that how often you are tested on each individual card will depend on how well you know it.  The idea is that through this spaced repetition, the new vocabulary/sentences/letters you learn will become embedded in your long term memory.  However, Anki is not a substitute for actually going out and using the vocabulary that you are learning through it.  It is advisable to try and learn a word in context, then put it into Anki and go out and start using it as soon as possible.</p>
      <p><h3>Installing Anki:</h3></p>
      <iframe width="640" height="480" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/C2Dz8kKavhI" frameborder="1" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
      <p><h3>Installing Anki:</h3><h5>(Text Version)</h5><p>
      <p>What you need to do first is download <a href="http://ankisrs.net/">Anki</a>. At the bottom of the page there are different download options, as Anki is available on both mac and PC.  Anki is also available on smartphone devices. The <b>iOS</b> version can be purchased <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/en/app/ankimobile-flashcards/id373493387?mt=8">here</a> for $24.99. The <b>Android</b> version can be downloaded <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ichi2.anki&hl=en">here</a> free of charge.</p>
	     <p>Once you have downloaded and installed Anki, you should go to the following website and create an account - <a href="https://ankiweb.net/ ">https://ankiweb.net/</a>Doing this will not only allow you to download shared decks, it will also allow you to synchronize your deck so that you can open up and use your own decks on your laptop/phone/ipad or someone else’s computer that has Anki installed.</p>
	     <p>Now find the button that says <b>‘get shared decks’</b> and click on it.  You will see a search option, and here you need to type <b><i>‘Khmer Language Manual’</i></b>.  When you do this a result will show, which is called <b>‘Khmer Language Manual 1-5’</b>. Click on the <b>‘info’</b> button, and then proceed to download this deck.  This is deck that we have created to help you as you go through the Khmer Language Manual.  As the book continues to develop, we will continue to create more decks.</p>
       <p> Once you have downloaded the deck, open it and it should be automatically added to the program.  When you close Anki, it will sync with ankiweb, and so the deck will also appear online and any cards you have studied will be recognized there.  This is only really an issue if you are studying on multiple computers or switching between your computer/ipad/smartphone etc.</p>
	<p><h5>Some other recommended decks to add are:</h5>
	<ul>
	<li>Vocabulary from Colloquial Cambodian</li>
	<li>Vocabulary from Christian Survival Guide.</li></ul> 
	<p>You can download those in exactly the same way as the previous deck, and use them with the Colloquial Cambodian book, or the Christian Survival Khmer book.</p><br><br><br>
