    <p><h3>Deck Setup:</h3>
      <p>The Khmer Language Manual deck is good for getting you started, but it is most likely that you will also want to create your own decks for new vocabulary that you learn yourself.</p>
      <p><iframe width="640" height="480" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/_sjRAsHTo8o" frameborder="1" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
      <p><h3>Deck Setup:</h3></p>
      <h5>(Text Version)</h5>
      <p>Go back to the Anki program itself, and click on the <b>‘create deck’</b> button.<br> <b>Input a name for your new deck.</b> Now your deck should appear on the main screen, and you can click on it.</p>
<p>At the top of the screen you will see 3 buttons: 
<ul>
<li>Decks</li>
<li>Add</li>
<li>Browse</li></ul></p>

<p>Decks will take you back to the previous screen so that you can see all of the decks you have available.  Browse will let you look through the flashcards in your individual decks.  For now we are concerned with adding cards to your deck, so click the add button.</p>  

At this point click on the button that says <b>'fields'</b>. Click <b>‘add’</b>, and then as the field name type in <b>‘Sentence’</b>.  This will give you the option to include a sentence in your flash card which will give you the word you are using in context.

Once you have done that, click <b>'close'</b>, and now click the cards button on the right of the fields button.  What you should see here is both a <b>forward</b> and <b>reverse</b> option at the top of the window.  If this is not the case, then please click the little plus button in the right hand corner.</p>
<p> You should now see two different card types, you need to make sure that these look opposite.  The first card type should say <b>(front)</b> in the box on the top right hand side of the window, and the second card type should say <b>(back)</b> in that same box.  If this is not the case, then select the second card type and click the <b>‘flip’</b> button.  You should now see <b>(back)</b> in the box on the top right hand side of the window.  This simply means that each time you add a new card, you will be tested both ways – from Khmer to English, and English to Khmer.  </p><br><br><br>
